#include<bits/stdc++.h>
#define get() getchar_unlocked()
using namespace std;
typedef long long int ll;
const int SIZE = 2e5+5;
ll arr[SIZE];
ll ff,ss;
int n;
inline int scan(void){
	    int n=0,s=1;
    char p=get();
    if(p=='-')  s=-1;
    while((p<'0'||p>'9')&&p!=EOF&&p!='-') p=get();
    if(p=='-') s=-1,p=get();
    while(p>='0'&&p<='9') { n = (n<< 3) + (n<< 1) + (p - '0'); p=get(); }
    return n*s;
}

inline ll scanL(void){
	    ll n=0,s=1;
    char p=get();
    if(p=='-')  s=-1;
    while((p<'0'||p>'9')&&p!=EOF&&p!='-') p=get();
    if(p=='-') s=-1,p=get();
    while(p>='0'&&p<='9') { n = (n<< 3) + (n<< 1) + (p - '0'); p=get(); }
    return n*s;
}
int main(int argc,char* argv[]){
    n = scan();
    ff = ss = 0LL;
    for(int i = 0;i<n;i++){
            arr[i] = scanL();
     if(arr[i]>ff)
        ss = ff,ff = arr[i];
     else if(arr[i]==ff)
        ss = ff;
     else if(arr[i]>ss)
        ss = arr[i];
    }
    printf("%lld %lld\n",ff,ss);
    return 0;
}
